data.text:
Who is Kim Kardashian dating? Who Kim Kardashian dated; list of Kim Kardashian loves, ex boyfriends; breakup rumors. List of Kim Kardashian's past relationships, exes and flings. The loves, exes and relationships of Kim Kardashian, listed by most recent (including baby daddy and spouse Kanye West). Learn Kim Kardashians' whole dating history here!

Kim Kardashian and husband Kanye West have four children together: daughter North "Nori" West, who was born June 15, 2013; son Saint West, who was born December 5, 2015, daughter Chicago West, who was born via surrogate January 15, 2018, and a son born via surrogate May 10, 2019.

Has Kim cheated on Kanye yet? Wonder if Kim will end up with another tape? Her first was such a hit, it seems like a sequel could be on the horizon. Regardless, check out her list of relationships below.

Kim Kardashian and Pete Davidson sparked dating rumors in October 2021, when they were seen holding hands while riding a roller coaster at Knott's Scary Farm in California.

A source claimed they were "just friends," saying, “They hang in the same circles, so they will be together from time to time. It’s just friends hanging out.”

In November 2021, Page Six reported that Davidson had arranged for a private dinner with Kim on Staten Island. She was also spotted in New York City, where Davidson lives. The two had kissed during an SNL skit earlier in October 2021.

In February 2022, Pete Davidson referred to Kardashian as his girlfriend while speaking with People (the TV Show!). Talking about what he does in his free time, he said, "Or, if I’m off, I just either hang with my friends or chill with my girlfriend inside. So I don’t do much."

Born and raised in Staten Island, New York, Pete Davidson, son of firefighter Scott Matthews Davidson, who tragically died during the 9/11 attacks, made a name for himself as an individual whose life story is filled with resilience and fortitude. Notably, his adolescent years were challenging, having been diagnosed with Crohn's disease at 17 and struggling with substance abuse. Despite the odds stacked against him, Davidson's ability to turn adversity into humor led him to a career in stand-up comedy. At the age of 20, Davidson found his footing on the hallowed stages of Saturday Night Live (SNL), being one of the youngest cast members in the long-running show's history. His tenure on SNL has been interspersed with numerous high-profile film and television roles, including parts in Trainwreck, The King of Staten Island, and Suicide Squad. Davidson's performances often shine a spotlight on his sharp wit and unique comedic style, often drawing from his own experiences, making him a relatable figure among his audience. Despite his fame and success, Davidson's personal life hasn't been without controversy. His mental health struggles became public fodder following a high-profile relationship with pop superstar Ariana Grande. Davidson's candidness about his Borderline Personality Disorder diagnosis have only heightened his visibility, turning him into something of a spokesperson for mental health issues. Through it all, Davidson's journey is truly a testament to the power of perseverance and the strength that can be found in vulnerability.

Born : 1993-11-16

Birthplace : Staten Island, New York, NY

Kim Kardashian and Kanye West started dating in 2012.

The pair were married in 2014 and have four children: daughter North "Nori" West (born June 15, 2013), son Saint West (born December 5, 2015), daughter Chicago West (born Jan. 15, 2019), and son Psalm West (born May 9, 2019).

It was reported in February 2021 that Kardashian filed for divorce from West after seven years of marriage.

Kim Kardashian was in a relationship with Kris Humphries 2011 - 2013. They were briefly married.

Kristopher Nathan Humphries (born February 6, 1985) is an American former professional basketball player who played in the National Basketball Association (NBA). He played in the NBA for the Utah Jazz, Toronto Raptors, Dallas Mavericks, New Jersey / Brooklyn Nets, Boston Celtics, Washington Wizards, Phoenix Suns, and the Atlanta Hawks. Humphries played college basketball for the Minnesota Golden Gophers of the University of Minnesota, and for the United States men's national basketball team.

Born : 02-06-1985

Birthplace : Minneapolis, Minnesota, USA

Rumor has it that Kim Kardashian had a fling with Michael Copon in 2010.

Michael Copon is an American actor and producer. He is known for playing Felix Taggaro in the television series One Tree Hill, Vin Keahi in the television series Beyond the Break, and Lucas Kendall in Power Rangers Time Force.

Born : 11-13-1982

Birthplace : Chesapeake, Virginia, USA

Kim Kardashian dated Miles Austin for a few months in 2010.

Miles Jonathon Austin III (born June 30, 1984) is an offensive assistant coach for the San Francisco 49ers of the National Football League (NFL) and a former American football wide receiver who played in the NFL for 10 seasons and spent the majority of his career with the Dallas Cowboys. He also was a member of the Cleveland Browns and Philadelphia Eagles. Austin played college football at Monmouth. Austin joined the Cowboys as an undrafted free agent in 2006 and was a member of the team for eight seasons. During his tenure with the Cowboys, he was named to two Pro Bowls. He retired after playing for the Browns and Eagles for one season each.

Born : 06-30-1984

Birthplace : Summit, New Jersey
